cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper investigates the compositional structure of message vectors computed by a deep network trained on a communication game, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of natural language processing (cs.CL), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper specifically focuses on the ability of neural representations to develop a "syntax" with functional analogues to qualitative properties of natural language, which is a common theme in these sub-categories. Therefore, cs.CL and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.AI, cs.CV, and cs.NE.
